00637, \"text\": \"Laura Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kimmince\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kimmince\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Jus the whole journey that I have been through to come to this moment and to finally win an Olympic medal for my country and represent them, it feels amazing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been 40 years since the U.S. men's gymnastics team last won a gold medal.\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9655344125856365, \"rank\": 0.027297931887144113, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA won gold in the team all-around in the 1984 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1538, \"end\": 1546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9533555625556304, \"rank\": 0.04890904614334654, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999622561979, \"rank\": 3.2514562941240544e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next is the men's gymnastics all-around final, which will be held on Wednesday, July 31, starting at 10:30 a.m. CT.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1729, \"end\": 1731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Time_Zone\", \"score\": 0.9999946935601931, \"rank\": 4.8786923387020196e-06, \"text\": \"CT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Time_Zone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Time_Zone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Top 24 individual gymnasts, with a maximum of two gymnasts per country, qualify for the men's all-around final.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Richard (10th place) and Juda (13th place) will represent Team USA.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1908, \"end\": 1916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9533555625556304, \"rank\": 0.04890904614334654, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top eight individual gymnasts on each apparatus qualify for the event finals, with, again, a maximum of two gymnasts per country per event.\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nedoroscik advanced to the pommel horse final.\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hong is the first reserve on still rings and vault (if anyone drops out, he will compete), while Richard is the third reserve on horizontal bar.\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's final, featuring seven-time Olympic medalist Simone Biles, takes place on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2316, \"end\": 2328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}]}"